metadata.title: Cessna 310
aws::graph::propositions: Military and Conversion Designations of Cessna 310
L-27A is the United States military designation for the Cessna 310A.
L-27A was later changed to U-3A.
L-27B is the United States military designation for the Cessna 310E/310M.
L-27B was later changed to U-3B.
U-3A is the L-27A redesignated in 1963.
U-3B is the L-27B redesignated in 1963.
Colemill Executive 600 is a conversion of Cessna 310F to 310Q models.
Colemill Executive 600 replaces the engines with 350 hp (260 kW) Lycoming TIO-540-J2BDs.
Riley 65 is a conversion offered for Cessna 310 to 310G models.
Riley 65 replaces the engines with two 240-260 hp (179–194 kW) Continental O-470Ds or -470Ms.
Riley Super 310 is a conversion of Cessna 310/320.
Riley Super 310 fits two 310 hp (231 kW) Continental TSIO-520J or 520N engines.

text:
L-27A
United States military designation for the 310A, later changed to U-3A.
L-27B
United States military designation for the 310E/310M, later changed to U-3B.
U-3A
L-27A redesignated in 1963.
U-3B
L-27B redesignated in 1963.
Colemill Executive 600
Conversion of models 310F to 310Q, replacing the engines with 350 hp (260 kW) Lycoming TIO-540-J2BDs driving four-bladed propellers.

Riley 65
Conversion offered for models 310 to 310G, replacing the engines with two 240-260 hp (179–194 kW) Continental O-470Ds or -470Ms.
Riley Super 310
Conversion of Cessna 310/320 by fitting two 310 hp (231 kW) Continental TSIO-520J or 520N engines.
